      "section_id": "MPS-0101",
      "selector": {
        "exact": "The present evidence boundary is decisive: nothing registered in this project establishes covert pooling of identifiable firm ontologies or default training on ordinary commercial content. Standard contractual language and repository safeguards weigh against the strongest hostile interpretation, although they do not prove flawless compliance, zero retention, or identical negotiated terms. Any future allegation should require authenticated contract, runtime, telemetry, or source-to-sink evidence. Until then, the appropriate output is a control program and research agenda, not a verdict about a named provider.",
