      "section_id": "MPS-0102",
      "selector": {
        "exact": "Exposure becomes strategically relevant only when a material signal leaves firm custody and some downstream actor is permitted and able to retain or generalize it. Connectors, feedback, support, telemetry, hosted skills, and managed agents create boundaries worth auditing, but a declared endpoint is not proof of transmission. The decisive questions are source, authority, payload, destination, retention, reuse, and customer control. Current registered evidence leaves the final runtime and contractual steps unknown, so the mechanism is a governance scenario rather than an allegation.",
