      "section_id": "MPS-0103",
      "selector": {
        "exact": "The Ajax Line is a unilateral governance recommendation: each firm should independently control its professional ontology, semantic derivatives, telemetry, evaluation use, portability, and exit. Practical controls include data-flow inventories, purpose and retention limits, tenant-isolated evaluation, auditable connector grants, deletion and export tests, and an architecture that preserves the ability to change providers. These measures do not guarantee security or competitive superiority, and coordinated vendor conduct requires separate legal analysis. Their value should be measured through exposure reduction, auditability, and credible exit.",
