      "section_id": "MPS-0103",
      "selector": {
        "exact": "Move 37 supplies a research horizon, not a prediction. AlphaGo demonstrated that search and learned evaluation in a closed game could select an unconventional action whose value became visible later. Legal strategy differs radically: duties, legitimacy, client objectives, incomplete information, and contested outcomes make evaluation harder. The useful lesson is to build contamination-resistant benchmarks for delayed-value legal strategy and to test surprising recommendations prospectively. The analogy does not establish an impending legal AlphaGo moment or a need for private firm data.",
